[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.924] Command (raw):
[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.924] CatGT
[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.924] Error: Missing -dir.
[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.924] 
[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.924] *** ERROR: MISSING CRITICAL PARAMETERS ***
[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.924] ------------------------
[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.924] Purpose:
[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.924] + Optionally join trials with given run_name and index ranges [ga,gb] [ta,tb]...
[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.924] + ...Or run on any individual file.
[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.924] + Optionally apply demultiplexing corrections.
[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.924] + Optionally apply band-pass and global CAR filters.
[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.925] + Optionally edit out saturation artifacts.
[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.925] + Optionally extract tables of sync waveform edge times to drive TPrime.
[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.925] + Optionally extract tables of other nonneural event times to be aligned with spikes.
[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.925] + Optionally join the above outputs across different runs (supercat feature).

[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.925] Output:
[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.925] + Results are placed next to source, named like this, with t-index = tcat:
[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.925] +    path/run_name_g5_tcat.imec1.ap.bin.
[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.925] + Errors and run messages are appended to CatGT.log in the current working directory.

[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.925] Usage:
[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.925] >CatGT -dir=data_dir -run=run_name -g=ga,gb -t=ta,tb <which streams> [ options ]

[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.925] Which streams:
[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.926] -ni                      ;required to process ni stream
[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.926] -ob                      ;required to process ob streams
[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.926] -ap                      ;required to process ap streams
[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.926] -lf                      ;required to process lf streams
[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.926] -obx=0,3:5               ;if -ob process these OneBoxes
[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.926] -prb_3A                  ;if -ap or -lf process 3A-style probe files, e.g., run_name_g0_t0.imec.ap.bin
[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.926] -prb=0,3:5               ;if -ap or -lf AND !prb_3A process these probes

[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.926] Options:
[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.926] -no_run_fld              ;older data, or data files relocated without a run folder
[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.926] -prb_fld                 ;input has folder-per-probe organization
[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.926] -prb_miss_ok             ;instead of stopping, silently skip missing probes
[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.927] -gtlist={gj,tja,tjb}     ;override {-g,-t} giving each listed g-index its own t-range
[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.927] -t=cat                   ;extract events from CatGT output files (instead of -t=ta,tb)
[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.927] -exported                ;apply FileViewer 'exported' tag to in/output filenames
[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.927] -t_miss_ok               ;instead of stopping, zero-fill if trial missing
[Thd 135169558379712 CPU 0 5/13/26 11:00:07.927] -zerofillmax=500         ;set a maximum zero-fill span (millisec)
